301.title: Around the Corner, Fidget's Made
301.plot: Alex and Erin attempt to create the world's biggest and fastest fidget spinner, Link's shield is put to the test when Alex attempts to ride it over treacherous terrain, and we terrify the hosts with giant bugs and electric shocks.

302.title: Back on the Saddle
302.plot: Alex and Erin practice their rodeo skills by riding each other using dad saddles, Erin disarms an explosive device with her hindquarters, and both hosts use their hot rods and giant balls to bring Rocket League into the real world.

303.title: Bad Math and Trashy Women
303.plot: Alex breaks down the geometry of an epic rooftop fail, Erin competes to decode bad cosplay in Trivia Attack, and a trashy ex drops by to surprise Alex with the secret she's been harboring for nine months.

304.title: Turret's Syndrome
304.plot: We build a real-life, paintball-loaded Portal Turret, and Alex goes for the win with some video game highlights. Plus, a do-nothing intern heads to Nevada.

305.title: Deadly Bushes & Dark Butts
305.plot: Alex and Erin test their skills on some of the Internet's weirdest indie games, fend off a murderous bush, and butt butts with the villains of Darksouls in an epic booty-controlled showdown.

306.title: Hide n' Sick
306.plot: Alex and Erin teach the Internet how to hide in plain sight, dig through their stockpile of VHS tapes to show some sick footage from the 1980s, and ask questionable questions to a couple of web-lebrities for prizes and punishments.

307.title: The Man Who Honks
307.plot: Alex and Erin greet the best honkin' guest of all time, take you through all three dimensions of Mario 64, and give Nintendo's Power Glove the finger - with fire.

308.title: Pan Puns & Killer Runs
308.plot: Alex and Erin grapple with a cast-iron step-dad, demolish computer parts for sport and show some Assassin's SPEED with real-life Assassin's Creed parkour.

309.title: Hand Washes and Bloodbaths
309.plot: Alex and Erin pit man versus beast to see which is the master finger licker, force video game characters to fight in a mascot deathmatch, and try to scrute an inscrutable nursery rhyme.

310.title: Cap'n Cram'n
310.plot: Alex and Erin compete to see whose big mouth fits the most stuff, and dig into some old cereal boxes to play a bunch of breakfast-y video games.

311.title: Bottom of the Box
311.plot: Alex and Erin dig through some sick VHS footage from the 90's and plunge into a giant cereal bowl to bob for breakfast-related CD ROMs.

312.title: All Sounds and No Backs
312.plot: Alex and Erin pull a wardrobe-related prank, and take shelter from a Bulletstorm using viewer sound effects.

191.title: Sara Underwood. Sara Underwood. Sara Underwood... And Some Other Guy
191.plot: Sara Underwood and Kevin Pereira are BACK together for the first time since 2012.

192.title: Lumbar Canyon and Back Again
192.plot: Apple conferences, PS4 Pros, and a DX Racer obstacle course showdown. Just another day in the life of The Attack.

193.title: Attack Space Program Administration
193.plot: The Attack makes Twitch history as we conduct the world's first let's play from space...sort of.

194.title: Pocketfuls of Regretti
194.plot: It's that time of the year again: leaves are turning brown, the wind has a delightful chill, and Eddie is once again being forced to eat against his will.

195.title: Typing of the Dead
195.plot: Alex and guest host, Kelly Link, take on the army of the undead armed with nothing more than WASD keyboards on this week's episode of The Attack.

196.title: Eddie's Audition
196.plot: Alex and guest host, Amy Vorpahl, spend some time looking at a bunch of bikini babes and make a shocking discovery.

197.title: Corrado Shave Club
197.plot: In their never-ending pursuit to get Corrado to shave his head, Ify and Alex accidentally publicly humiliate Eddie. Just kidding, we've been planning it for weeks.

198.title: Return of the Spaghetti
198.plot: It's that time of the year again: leaves are turning brown, the wind has a delightful chill, and Eddie is once again being forced to eat against his will.

199.title: Hot Pepper Torture!
199.plot: A harmless game of Taters, Please gets spicy when hot peppers get introduced to the mix.

200.title: Sara Underwood Snapchats Alex
200.plot: Sara Underwood is back and Alex is just as nervous as ever as we hop on the sub-train and relive some of The Attack's finest moments to date.

201.title: Jurrasic Head Shave
201.plot: The Attack fam deal with Dino DNA and the aftermath of episode 200. Will Corrado's hair ever be the same?

202.title: Blimp Lives Matter
202.plot: Bet you didn't know Alex had a great grandfather who flew blimps during the war.

203.title: Exclusive Overwatch Characters
203.plot: Things are getting spooky at the Attack office with new Overwatch characters and a whole lot more.

204.title: Seinfeld Socker Boppers and Girl Fights
204.plot: Coral and Saige go head-to-head no-holds battle to the death in the Loot Crate Thunderdome. Two women enter, one woman leaves.

205.title: Playstation VR: Worth It?!?
205.plot: Come one, come all for the only PlayStation VR review that matters.

207.title: Nintendo Switch Exclusive Reveal
207.plot: The Nintendo Switch is finally here and we have an exclusive unaired reveal trailer for Nintendo's biggest console.

208.title: Dark Souls Butt Controller Challenge
208.plot: On today's show we attempt the hardest game of Dark Souls 3 ever, played co-operatively with nothing but player's butts.

209.title: First Livestream from Space
209.plot: The Attack Space Service Administration is back, and this time, we're sending Space Invader to space. And turning it on this time.

210.title: Slave Leia and Harambe
210.plot: The spookiest episode to date as The Attack crew conduct the very first Halloween Costume Contest and revive our dearly departed, Harambe.

211.title: Attack on Titanfall Battle Royale
211.plot: Two Titans enter, one Titan leaves in this no-holds barred battle to the death.

212.title: Cat Poop Dunk Tank
212.plot: No life insurance, but we're still dunking the entire Attack Staff in a tank full of ice cold cat poop.

213.title: Broken Olympic Dreams and TVS
213.plot: Special guest Jon Carnage joins us for a very special Attackskimo Olympics.

214.title: Fruit-Crushing Thighs and Horny Turtles
214.plot: An extra-heavy dose of the Pile as we drink thigh-made smoothies and fight off amorous turtles.

215.title: Berdday Boy Mouse Trap & Omgitsfirefoxx
215.plot: It's his birdday, and he can cry if he wants to.

216.title: Pokemon Sun and Moon IRL Spandex Battles
216.plot: We review Pokemon Sun and Moon and decide once and for all which generation is best.

217.title: Hologram Crystal Light Challenge
217.plot: We hear lots of kids are taking the Crystal Light Challenges, so naturally we had to throw our hat in the ring.

218.title: Throwdown
218.plot: We test the durability of Eddie's stomach as we subject him to the most dangerous substance know to man: Fruit Roll-Ups.

219.title: Best Controller of All Time
219.plot: In the Pile we reveal how Joe Rogan reacted to a man punching a goddamn animal. Also resident witch Steebs gets tarred and feathered with caramel and popcorn.

220.title: Final Fantasy 15 IRL Challenge!
220.plot: We took the best part of Final Fantasy 15 and tried it out IN REAL LIFE boys. "Now I know how the Japanese feel" -Jennifer Murphy 2016.

221.title: Man Punches Kangaroo!
221.plot: In the Pile we reveal how Joe Rogan reacted to a man punching a goddamn animal. To be fair that kangaroo was a dick. Also resident witch Steebs gets tarred and feathered with caramel and popcorn.

222.title: Tinder Hijacked by Kevin Pereira!!!
222.plot: Kevin dropped by the show and hijacked Alex's Tinder profile, with mixed results. Also, Alex tries to prove he's the Smoothest Guy ever (that dank Event Horizon ref, tho).

223.title: The Last Guardian Dog Challenge
223.plot: The Last Guardian is out so we brought a dog into the studio to see if it could survive an obstacle course based on the game. RIP little puppy.

224.title: Rock Paper Scissors Deathmatch!
224.plot: Alex presides over the American version of the Japanese Rock Paper Scissors Tournament. Thanks for being on the show, The Rock!!!.

225.title: Hannukah Beats Christmas?
225.plot: Yaniv brings some diversity to the most racially insensitive Holiday special to date. Also, we hosted some local mariachis on their Pre-Deportation Tour.

226.title: Canadian OMGitsfirefoxx Face Lick
226.plot: After a harrowing encounter with a weird Mario, Alex and Sonja endure the trials of the Canadian New Year.

227.title: Cup Noodles vs. Top Ramen Showdown
227.plot: Alex becomes a tabloid superstar, and we see who wins in the Ultimate Noodle Championship: Cup Noodles or Top Ramen!? Two meals enter, one meal leaves.

228.title: Google Home Love???
228.plot: Can A.I. feel love? Well, they sure don't love Alex.

229.title: Awesome James Done Quick
229.plot: It's that time of the year again. AJDQ - Awesome James Done Quick.

230.title: Video Game Jeopardy!
230.plot: The first ever game of Video Game Jeopardy took place with a special guest appearance by the Mayor of Los Angeles.

231.title: Rhythm Game One Band Challenge
231.plot: Rhythm games are fun, but you know what's more fun? All of the rhythm games. Just watch the video.

232.title: Navage vs. Neti Pot
232.plot: Put this in your nose and drain it. Alex and Erin test out the Navage and the Neti Pot as we go Into The Amazon-e.

233.title: Biting Chocolate Furniture?!
233.plot: Let's dive into the Greenlight District and play a round of INANIMATE OBJECT CHOMPAGHEDDON.

234.title: Resident Evil 7 IRL
234.plot: We test out the old school fixed camera perspective. In a real-life obstacle course, filled with zombies.

235.title: Razer Keyboard Hats
235.plot: We test out the old school fixed camera perspective. In a real-life obstacle course, filled with zombies.

236.title: Heely Kneivel
236.plot: Alex shows us that Heelys are the WHEEL DEAL, and Erin challenges him to prove the skills. Spoiler: it doesn't go well.

237.title: Doctor Disregard
237.plot: Another day in The Attack studios. With special guest, Doctor Disregard. Or Alex?

238.title: Where's Poochy
238.plot: Today on The Attack, a game review rap battle, a hardcore tattoo challenge, and a little Hoop and Stick action. Plus, a marshmallow fluff surprise.

239.title: Cruising and Curling
239.plot: Let's take those old records off the shelf - PLUS, ERIN GETS A NEW HAT.

240.title: All Cruise Everything
240.plot: It's that episode of The Attack where everything goes Tom Cruise Crazy! You'll never know when a wild Tom Cruise appears. It's his power - and his curse.

241.title: Drink Download!
241.plot: Singer-songwriter and Attack of the Show alumni Zachariah Selwyn joins us for a special episode of The Attack. But we take an unexpected turn when he tries to hijack the show and tells everyone to drop a load in their mouths.

242.title: Rockstar Battle Stream with Wavves
242.plot: On today's episode, we sit down with Wavves and beat up our crew with Antwon. Blake Anderson joins us to play some online GTA for the Rockstar Battle Stream.

243.title: Key Sports Typing Sides Tournament
243.plot: The biggest thing since lawn mower racing, it's THE KEYSPORTS TYPING SIDES TOURNAMENT. With special guest and eSports shoutcasting superstar, NATHANIEL FABRIKANT.

244.title: Minesweeper Madness with Kryozgaming!
244.plot: Minesweeper, smashing, KRYOZGAMING, Attack on Halo Wars 2, and the HOTTEST HOT AND STREAMY yet.

245.title: Club Penguin Mom Speed Run
245.plot: Alex and Erin's moms help get them both banned from Club Penguin! Plus, Yaniv rolls in to talk about music, and Alex goes on an IRL journey of self-discovery.

246.title: The Legend of Iron Crotch
246.plot: Today: Erin in a burglar's shirt, The Legend of Iron Crotch, and a brand new segment: "SICK FOOTAGE". Plus, the planets get Hot N' Streamy.

247.title: Breath of the Wild Sclusives
247.plot: We can't believe it either. The very first review of The Legend of Zelda: Breath of the Wild happened in our studio. Plus, our friend Morgan Jay comes by to share some of the original music he contributed to the OST.

248.title: Switch Destruction
248.plot: Erin has to learn that being late has consequences. Even on Switch release day. So we let the audience decide the fate of her Switch: SAVE or SMASH?

249.title: Blark and Tall Boy Son
249.plot: Today, we've got a VERY special guest: Alex's dad, Blark. We taste The Legend of Zelda: Breath of The Wild. And ALSO - we get into some SICK FOOTAGE.

250.title: 1-2 Switch Life
250.plot: Coral and Joey review 1-2 Switch for the Nintendo Switch. Jason goes to Whole Foods. And Alex and Erin get into the real world implications of 1-2 Switch's Mini-games.

251.title: Farewell to Eddie
251.plot: The internet decides if we fire Eddie. Concrete diving. Fitness.

252.title: Chugging Clamato = Job Security
252.plot: Last week, our amazing community chose to FIRE Eddie. He's back in the studio to apply and interview for his old job. With the help of Clamato.

253.title: Bad Breath of the Wild
253.plot: We show Link what dubious food really looks AND tastes like in Bad Breath of The Wild challenge. Plus, Will Smith goes for a jump. We take a stroll through the Green Light District.

254.title: Erin Pilots the Ship!
254.plot: While Alex and the dads are away, Erin and the team will play. Steebz the Weebz, Nick-san, Coral's Rose Ceremony, and Jeo-Parody. Oh - and Dynfeld.

255.title: Diggin Nuts & Dodging Arrows
255.plot: It's an arrow-dodging Monday with a visit from Coral, The Rap God. Alex and Erin get to meet Dugnuts, Doug Nut, and Dig Nut. Plus, things go sideways during Sick Footage.

256.title: Let's Get Mass Correct
256.plot: Erin and Alex get down for home automation (R.O.M.A.N.), and for Jason explaining the internet. It's a Wednesday with Fem-Nick reviewing Mass Effect: Andromeda, and with a classic game of Mass Correct. Plus: SPACE SUITS.

257.title: Cram That Craw!
257.plot: Alex and Erin CRAM THAT CRAW. Steeb the Weeb takes a look at "Your Name" and eat some balut. Who wins Stream of The Week!? And Nick drops a tray.

258.title: Spring Cleaving
258.plot: Clad in Futureman Gaming attire, our resident Celery, Alex Corea, and Cinnamon Bun Queen Erin Steeby cleave out the cobwebs. Eddie falls asleep in Skittles. Sick Footage for your baby.

259.title: Paintball Pop Quiz
259.plot: Paintball geography pop quiz. Jason explains SPORTS. ALIENS!. And way more things. Like, EXPLOSIONS!!!.

260.title: Nerf Battle Royale
260.plot: It's not a Friday if we can't battle to the death. 6 members of our squad enter the Attack-ter-dome, and only ONE can leave with their life.

261.title: Mirror Masters
261.plot: Sick Footage of Mr. Baby Proofer. Erin's turn in the Staff Infection. Headset destruction in Hot and Streamy. All of our ideas for April Fools Jokes. PLUS, MIRROR MAKEUP.

262.title: Videos That Ended Too Early Theatre
262.plot: Today we let the Twitch community decide the fate of "Videos That Ended Too Early Theatre", we review the new Razor Blade Stealth laptop, and Jason explains airplanes?

263.title: Attack's Attack on Titan
263.plot: In today's episode, we discuss Japanese food and culture, Attack on Titan, and Alex gets whacked by a kindo stick for improper dining etiquette in our new installment of "Steeb the Weeb".

264.title: Tap Off
264.plot: Alex and Erin test the funny meter. We watch "Tackling Football: A Woman's Guide to Understanding the Game" in Sick Footage. There's ANOTHER erotic video from Corrado is Staff Infection. AND WE PLAY TAPPER IN REAL LIFE, FOR KEEPS.

265.title: Ikea Smash Off!
265.plot: Cheap Swedish Furniture must be destroyed. Soldiers and bayonets. Jason in cars. Joey loves Yooka-Laylee. AND MORE.

266.title: World's Longest Big Wheel Race
266.plot: Erin is scared of rocks. Nick in Japan. And, more important that everything else in the history of life - THE WORLD'S LONGEST BIG WHEEL RACE.

267.title: Solid Snake and Link: Lady Killers
267.plot: Erin kills camouflaged Eddie. Solid Snake kills Erin. Squatfest 2017. Falling off of cabinets! Indie games in The Start Tank. Sick Footage teaches you "HOW TO STUDY"! AND, HOT MANNEQUINS!!!.

268.title: Crappy Cosplay
268.plot: Erin gives Alex his fifteen minutes of internet fame but they get cut short when a fan shows up. Coral, Erin, and Yaniv play Trivia Attack. And we share our VRLA experience in The Pile.

269.title: Attack Speedrun
269.plot: The gang speedruns The Attack. Head and crotch hitting in the pile, and Kevin's parents play The Barelywed Game.

270.title: Lego Foot Torture
270.plot: Alex and Erin torture themselves in The Great Lego Caper. Russian kids show their idea of fun in The Pile. Also, Gumbo as a weapon?

271.title: Call of Duty: WW2 & Hardware Graveyard
271.plot: Erin trains to fight. Call of Duty answers a call - of duty. Alex refills his HP. We wander into the Hardware Graveyard. Plus, things get Hot and Streamy.

272.title: Gladiator Combat
272.plot: Smashing and bashing, all of the tension from this season has come to a competitive climax in THE ATTACK GLADIATOR DUEL. Two hosts enter, one host leaves.

-1.title: April Fool's Pranks and Sling Shot Burritos
-1.plot: Alex and Erin's minds and bodies get fully synced. We slingshot a burrito at Eddie. Mr. Babyyyy Proofer? And more interesting videos in Sick Footage -- including Erin Steeby's old film school project.
